In [42]:
def predictVec(X, Sigma, means):
    p = []
    for i in range(10):
        det = np.linalg.det(Sigma[i])
        if np.abs(det) < 1e-12:
            eig_values, _ = np.linalg.eig(Sigma[i])
            det = np.product(eig_values[eig_values > 1e-12])
            inv = np.linalg.pinv(Sigma[i])
        else:
            inv = np.linalg.inv(Sigma[i])
        pi = 1/((2*np.pi)**(len(means[i])) * det) ** (1/2)
        pi *= np.exp(-1/2*((X - means[i]) @ inv @ (X - means[i]).T ))
        pi = pi.diagonal()
        p.append(pi)

    return np.array(p)

t = time()
probs = np.real(predictVec(test_data, Sigma, means).T)
sums = probs.sum(axis=1)
sums[probs.sum(axis=1) == 0] = 1
probs = probs / sums.reshape((-1,1))
predicted = np.argmax(probs, axis=1)
print("My GBC testing time: ", time() - t)

Covariance Matrice was singular and was not invertiable and also had determinant of zero.

I had to use pseudo determinant and pseudo inverse to do the job.

My KNN¶

In [28]:
def euclidean_dists(X, X_train):
    X2 = (X**2).sum(axis=1).reshape((X.shape[0], 1)) * np.ones((1, X_train.shape[0]))
    XT2 = (X_train**2).sum(axis=1) * np.ones((X.shape[0], 1))
    XXT = X @ X_train.T
    dists = np.sqrt(X2 + XT2 - 2*XXT)
    return dists
def KNN_predict(dists, k):
    max_args = dists.argsort()[:, :k]
    votes = pd.DataFrame(max_args).applymap(lambda x: train_label[x])
    predict = votes.mode(axis=1)[0]
    return predict
